Class GPXImporter

java.lang.Object
  ultigpx.GPXImporter
All Implemented Interfaces:
GPXImporterExporterConstants
public class GPXImporter
extends java.lang.Object
implements GPXImporterExporterConstants

Class GPX Importer is used for importing a file into the UltiGPXFile structure. It uses JDOM for processing XML. For more information about JDOM visit http://www.jdom.org/ This class was written for the project for CPSC 301, Winter 2008

Author:
Jill Ainsworth

importGPX

public static void importGPX(Group inputGroup,
                             java.lang.String filename)
                      throws org.jdom.JDOMException,
                             java.io.IOException
importGPX imports a GPX file to a group. The filename is given as a string, and the group is given. If there are any problems with the file, either a JDOMException or an IO Exception is thrown

Parameters:
filename - a String, the name of the file you want to import
inputGroup - a Group, contains the tracks, routes, and waypoints that were in the file after this method is run
Throws:
org.jdom.JDOMException - if a problem occurs when importing the file
java.io.IOException - if a problem occurs when importing the file

importUltiGPX

public static void importUltiGPX(Database inputDatabase,
                                 java.lang.String filename)
                          throws org.jdom.JDOMException,
                                 java.io.IOException
importGPX imports an UltiGPX file to a database. The filename is given as a string, a Database is given. If there are any problems with the file, either a JDOMException or an IO Exception is thrown Because importUltiGPX imports groups from the file and groups can not be nested, you can not import an UltiGPX file to a group

Parameters:
filename - a String, the name of the file you want to import
inputDatabase - a Database, contains the tracks, routes, and waypoints that were in the file after this method is run
Throws:
org.jdom.JDOMException - if a problem occurs when importing the file
java.io.IOException - if a problem occurs when importing the file

getTimeOld

private static double getTimeOld(java.lang.String toParse)
Deprecated. 

Get Time Old extracks the time from the GPXFile. Time in a GPX file is stored as YYYY_MM_DDTHH:MM:SSZ This method uses a Gregorian calendar to then convert this into time in milis. This method is private because it is only used when importing GPX files If there is a formating problem, the defalut time is returned This method is old, and has been replaced by getTime, do not use this method

Parameters:
toParse - a String, the string representing time in the GPX file
Returns:
double the time in milis since 1970

getTime

private static long getTime(java.lang.String toParse)
Get Time extracks the time from the GPXFile. Time in a GPX file is stored as YYYY_MM_DDTHH:MM:SSZ This method uses a Simple Date Format to parse the date into a long. This method is private because it is only used when importing GPX files This method replaces getTimeOld If there is a formating problem, the default time is returned

Parameters:
toParse - a String, the string representing time in the GPX file
Returns:
long the time
